Basic Installation
==================

The simplest way to compile this package is in Ubuntu 10.04 (Lucid Lynx):

  1. `cd' to the directory containing the package's source code and type
     `qmake-qt3 -o Makefile kflog.pro'

  2. Type `make' to compile the package.

  3. Type `make install' to install the programs and data files. The program
     can be found in the subdir release. The data files are stored in your
     home directory and can be accessed by typing `cd ~/.kflog/'

  4. You can remove the program binaries and object files from the
     source code directory by typing `make clean'.
